Package randomartassignment.expression

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ExpressionGeneratorParallel
    ExpressionGeneratorParallel is essentially a wrapper around ExpressionParallel in that it represents a whole expression along with associated methods that help create it and evaluate it.
    ExpressionParallel
    ExpressionParallel represents a mathematical "expression," by which is meant either a representation of a variable, a mathematical operator, or a mathematical function (such as those of trigonometry).
    ExpressionParallel.Average
    Average represents the operation of averaging (i.e. the mean).
    ExpressionParallel.Cos
    Cos represents the trigonometric operation cosine.
    ExpressionParallel.Multiply
    Multiply represents the operator *.
    ExpressionParallel.Sin
    Sin represents the trigonometric operator sine.
    ExpressionParallel.Variable
    Variable represents a mathematical variable - to be replaced with actual values when evaluated as part of a larger expression.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    ExpressionGeneratorParallel.ExpressionType
    A list of all expressions known to ExpressionGeneratorParallel.
